==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Creatinin
<hw>Cre*at"i*nin</hw> <pr>(kr?-?t"?-n?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A white, crystalline, nitrogenous body
closely related to creatin but more basic in its properties, formed from
the latter by the action of acids, and occurring naturally in muscle
tissue and in urine.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>kretinine</asp>.]</altsp><-- = creatinine, C4H7N3O -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

